      "content": "that makes sense. i mean, i thought it was just me being paranoid, but you're saying it's actually a thing. if they're already using it for \"recommendations,\" how would they go about using it to actually monitor someone specifically? like, could they use the sensors in a smart home to build a profile on my mental state in real time? it feels way more targeted than just \"tailored services.\"",
